FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44802
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776877554
OL,3,CNI Water appears before MLAs to
OL,4,Cdiscuss its impact on Lough Neagh
OL,5,Cpollution
OL,7,FIt comes as NI Water faces severe
OL,8,Ffunding pressures as blue green algae
OL,9,Fhas already been spotted on the lough
OL,10,Fthis year.
OL,12,FPollution and Lough Neagh, two terms
OL,13,Fnow synonymous with each other.
OL,15,FBlue Green Algae has clung to the
OL,16,Flough over the last few summers and
OL,17,Fhas already returned this year.
OL,18,FBringing to the surface a deep rooted
OL,19,Fproblem.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44803
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776877554
OL,3,CNI Water appears before MLAs to
OL,4,Cdiscuss its impact on Lough Neagh
OL,5,Cpollution
OL,7,FOne of the main causes of pollution is
OL,8,Fexcessive amounts of phosphorus in the
OL,9,Fwater.
OL,11,FToday, in front of MLAs at a joint
OL,12,FAgriculture and Infrastructure
OL,13,FCommittee meeting Northern Ireland
OL,14,Fwater said it was responsible for
OL,15,Froughly 20% of the phosphorus that
OL,16,Fmakes its way into the Lough each year.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776877554
OL,3,CNI Water appears before MLAs to
OL,4,Cdiscuss its impact on Lough Neagh
OL,5,Cpollution
OL,7,FDr Garry Curran, Director of
OL,8,FEngineering and Sustainability
OL,9,Faddressed MLAs by first saying: "Lough
OL,10,FNeagh's water quality problems are
OL,11,Freal, serious and long-standing, with
OL,12,Fa focus on blue-green algae they are
OL,13,Fdriven by excess phosphorus entering
OL,14,Fthe lough over many years alongside
OL,15,Fwarmer weather and wider ecological
OL,16,Fpressures."
OL,26,@xD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44805
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776877554
OL,3,CNI Water appears before MLAs to
OL,4,Cdiscuss its impact on Lough Neagh
OL,5,Cpollution
OL,7,F"Phosphorus enters the lough from many
OL,8,Fdifferent activities across the whole
OL,9,Fcatchment. These include agriculture,
OL,10,Fthrough septic tanks, urban run off
OL,11,Fand specifically for Northern Ireland
OL,12,FWater, or treated waste water.
OL,26,@oD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776877554
OL,3,CNI Water appears before MLAs to
OL,4,Cdiscuss its impact on Lough Neagh
OL,5,Cpollution
OL,7,F"Across the Lough Neagh catchment,
OL,8,Faround 545 tonnes of phosphorus enters
OL,9,FNI Water's sewage network. Around 99%
OL,10,Fof that is conveyed to waste water
OL,11,Ftreatment works. On average around 88%
OL,12,Fof the phosphorus is removed during
OL,13,Ftreatment. As a result around 65
OL,14,Ftonnes per year are returned to the
OL,15,Fcatchment.
OL,17,F"Around five tonnes per year, roughly
OL,18,F1% can be lost from the network. Taken
OL,19,Ftogether NI Water returns around 70
OL,20,Ftonnes per year."
OL,26,@oD@AOUyD@AOU|D@QO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G6/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776877554
OL,3,CNI Water appears before MLAs to
OL,4,Cdiscuss its impact on Lough Neagh
OL,5,Cpollution
OL,7,FThis accounts for roughly 20% of the
OL,8,Ftotal number of phosperhous that
OL,9,Fenters the lough each year.
OL,11,FFor campaigners, an official figure
OL,12,Ffrom NI Water on its own pollution
OL,13,Flevels is appreciated, but there are
OL,14,Ffears that number could be much higher.
OL,16,FJames Orr from the campaign group
OL,17,FFriends of the Earth said "That's
OL,18,Fprobably an underestimate. First of
OL,19,Fall we don't have what we call EDMs,
OL,20,Fthese monitors on every sewage
OL,21,Fdischarge. So we don't really know.
OL,26,@yD@[OU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44808
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776877554
OL,3,CNI Water appears before MLAs to
OL,4,Cdiscuss its impact on Lough Neagh
OL,5,Cpollution
OL,7,F"Also we have an issue with something
OL,8,Fto do with flow compliance and that is
OL,9,Fwhere pollution gets diverted, raw
OL,10,Fpollution, raw sewage into waterways
OL,11,Fthat feed into Lough Neagh and that
OL,12,Fhasn't been properly calculated. 20%
OL,13,Fis an awful lot but it is still an
OL,14,Funderestimate.
OL,26,@oD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,449,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F448A1776877554
OL,3,CNI Water appears before MLAs to
OL,4,Cdiscuss its impact on Lough Neagh
OL,5,Cpollution
OL,7,FOther issues discussed in the joint
OL,8,Fcommittee included well known
OL,9,Fconstraints with NI Water funding,
OL,10,Fwhich limits its ability to reduce its
OL,11,Fphosphorus output. As well as concerns
OL,12,Faround the taste and flavour of
OL,13,Fdrinking water.
OL,15,FAs Northern Ireland water officials
OL,16,Fmade clear, they are responsible for
OL,17,Fonly a limited percentage of the
OL,18,Fpollution problems around Lough Neagh.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
